@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
@contentType = application/json

# Asignar/quitar el rol root ahora exige un token con rol ROOT (admin puede
# gestionar cualquier rol EXCEPTO admin/root).

### 0. Login como root (necesario para gestionar el rol root)
# @name loginRoot
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "{{rootUserName}}",
  "password": "{{rootPassword}}"
}

### 1. Asignar rol root al usuario compartido (userId + roleIdRoot)
POST {{baseUrl}}/user-role
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{loginRoot.response.body.$.access_token}}

{
  "id_user": "{{userId}}",
  "id_role": "{{roleIdRoot}}"
}

### 2. Ver roles asignados al usuario (un usuario puede tener varios)
GET {{baseUrl}}/user-role/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{loginRoot.response.body.$.access_token}}
Accept: application/json

### 3. Login para confirmar el rol "root" en el JWT
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "{{clienteUserName}}",
  "password": "{{clientePassword}}"
}

### 4. Probar acceso a endpoint que solo permite root (asignar permisos a un rol)
POST {{baseUrl}}/roles/{{roleIdAdmin}}/permissions
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.$.access_token}}

{
  "permissionIds": []
}

### 5. Desactivar el rol root (sin eliminar la asignación)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/user-role/{{userId}}/{{roleIdRoot}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{loginRoot.response.body.$.access_token}}

{
  "active": false
}

### 6. Login otra vez: "root" ya NO debe aparecer en roles
# @name loginSinRoot
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "{{clienteUserName}}",
  "password": "{{clientePassword}}"
}

### 7. Repetir el endpoint solo-root: ahora debe dar 403
POST {{baseUrl}}/roles/{{roleIdAdmin}}/permissions
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{loginSinRoot.response.body.$.access_token}}

{
  "permissionIds": []
}

### 8. Reactivar el rol root
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/user-role/{{userId}}/{{roleIdRoot}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{loginRoot.response.body.$.access_token}}

{
  "active": true
}

### 9. Quitar por completo la asignación del rol root (cleanup)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/user-role/{{userId}}/{{roleIdRoot}}
Authorization: Bearer {{loginRoot.response.body.$.access_token}}
Accept: application/json
